===Adjective===
'''topless''' (''no comparative or superlative'')

#lacking a [[top]]
#(''especially of a woman'') Not wearing a [[garment]] covering the top half of the body; [[naked]] from the [[waist]] up.
#* ''The [[council]] voted to allow '''topless''' swimmers on the beach.''
# Involving women that are naked from the waist up, often [[stripper]]s or [[dancer]]s.
#* ''Only her closest friends knew that Jenny was working at a '''topless''' bar to help with college expenses.''
#* ''Fred didn't tell his wife that the convention had involved a fair amount of '''topless''' entertainment.''
# ''(automotive):'' a [[convertible]] car having the top retracted or otherwise open

